<br>
OK, just kidding.<br>
<br>
I still don't see a lot of mages, but I am starting to see more (in my amazing month or so on FV) new mages on Faydwer. On this server, our summoned items seem to be actually useful and valuable, as compared to a typical blue server with 8 zillion twinks in planar gear whacking orc pawns in Greater Faydark. You do sometimes have to educate other folks as to what you can summon - the new Luclin items, especially. And if they never played a mage on their old server, they might not be aware of the nice magical weapons and stacks of bandaids and 100% weight-reduction packs and such that we've always had.<br>
<br>
Learn how to hunt effectively with a pet, keep your Bind Wounds skill maxed and bandaids on hand, equip your fellow groupies (and their pets) with your summoned stuff, use your nifty little damage shield on the tanks, and nuke as needed.<br>
<br>
