<br>
Elizer - true, but the 'end game' should always be a consideration. I have known too many people that picked a class only because it was great at soloing, like a hybrid, only to be sorely disappointed in the 51+ guild game.<br>
<br>
The mage is a guild raid friendly and usefull class between summoned focus items, mod rods, and coth.<br>
<br>
As far as choice of race goes? It really matters little in the long run. Items can go a long way to makeing up for a slightly lower starting int, or whatever. Pick a race you enjoy.<br>
<br>
Don't pick a halflink for the 4% exp bonus or the 118 wis as a druid; Don't pick an eruditz because of the high int for your wiz. Don't pick a Troll for the regen.<br>
<br>
Pick the race/class combo that YOU want to play. 118 versus 110 starting wis, or natural regen, etc... all trivial, if not meaningless by your 50's (or sooner).<br>
